    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Washington</name>, <date when="1870-07-21" rend="right">July 21, 1870</date>. </dateline>
                <salute>My dear friend,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I have just received your letter of the 7th inst. I appreciate your kindness in the
                matter of the poem.<ptr target="col.00003_n1"/> I
                send herewith a verbatim copy of Emerson's note,<ptr target="col.00003_n2"/> as
                requested.</p>

            <p>Nothing very new or special with me, these days. I am well as usual—am still
                employed in the Attorney General's Office. A new edition of my book will be printed
                this fall, with another small volume in prose.<ptr target="col.00003_n3"/> You shall have
                early copies, may-be in sheets.</p>

            <p>Farewell for the present. I send you my love—Write whenever you can.</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
